candidates.title: feat: add sorted_set_union_store and sorted_set_length_by_score + upgrades
candidates.body:
- Adds two new sorted set methods: `sorted_set_length_by_score` and `sorted_set_union_store`.
- Upgrades the client protos version in order to get `sorted_set_union_store` protos.
- Updates `sorted_set_get_rank` to accept `SortedSetOrder` as an optional argument.

candidates.body:
I may have to leave the bug bash a little early so started early with the Rust SDK. This might have been in your backlog/WIP already but since I was about to follow examples pattern anyway, just decided to PR it.

my_momento_store was created

candidates.title: chore: remove legacy jwt token support
candidates.body:
Remove jwt support from the credential provider. They don't work correctly for storage and haven't been used for some time.

Remove now unneeded jsonwebtoken dependency.

candidates.title: feat: improve NotFound handling, return Optional for storage get
candidates.body:
This is a POC for addressing some of the things that we ran into in the other SDKs; namely:

1. Split up NotFound errors into distinct categories
2. Change GetResponse value to Optional, to allow us to distinguish between NotFound and WrongType

Also removes the inner `Success` enum value from the GetResponse because it was making it harder to work with the success case, and in the Cache client, we don't use enums when we only have a single response type.

Open to feedback on all of the above.
